    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Door Striker Pin</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Door Striker Pin</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Removal procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Striker pin procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1603855" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603855.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Striker Pin</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. DOOR LOCK PILLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. STRIKER PIN</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The striker pin provides for positive engagement with the door latch assembly. Removal and
                        installation requires a Torx head tool. Enlarged mounting holes in door lock pillar and mounting
                        plate allow adjustment.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bolts securing striker pin to door lock pillar.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove striker pin.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Installation procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Striker pin procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install striker pin and secure to door lock pillar with two bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603855">Figure 74</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts to 19 to 24 Lbf-ft (26 to 33 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
